// TUNING PARAMETERS:
// UniqueCountries >= 2: Minimum countries (2 = baseline)
// TimeDifferenceMinutes <= 120: Time window threshold (60min = stricter, 240min = looser)
// ResultType == 0: Only successful logins (can include failed with ResultType != 0)
// LocationDetails filtering: Adjust based on false positive rate
// Distance threshold: Use 900km for general, 500km for strict, 1500km for loose

// NOTES:
// - Impossible travel = strong indicator of account compromise
// - Average flight speed = 900 km/hour (500 km practical minimum)
// - 2-hour window = most suspicious (tight timeframe, long distance)
// - VPNs can complicate detection (appear in different countries)
// - Business travel may generate legitimate alerts (account owner traveling)
// - Review SourceIPs - same IP for both logins = false positive (VPN)
// - Corporate VPN users may appear in different countries (false positives)
// - Newly compromised accounts show this pattern immediately
// - Correlate with failed login attempts before successful login
// - Can combine with risk score from other detections
// - Consider time zones and shift workers for false positive reduction
// - Multiple countries in single day = check if legitimate business travel
